===subject:Maybe we should worry
===from:Leah Pollastrini
===date:Tue Feb 15 15:34:18 2000
===message:	In your message you state,"if science really can't back up that there is a problem affecting society, there shouldn't be a big worry."  I disagree with this opinion.  I believe that until science can prove there is definately no harm to humans, ecosystems, populations, environments, etc. we should worry because through worry comes research and answers.  Simply because we haven't seen any immediate problems doesn't mean there aren't any.  Only through extensive research can we prove if something is completely safe, and only then should it be approved for use.  
